Preheat your #oven{} (for the tortillas) to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm chunks.

Zest half a @lime{1/2} (per 2P). Chop into four wedges.

Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{2}.

Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%pack}.

> TIP: If you want to avoid turning on the oven you can dry-fry the tortillas in a pan instead.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat (without oil).

Once the pan is hot, fry the @Irish beef mince{240%g} until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.
IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Add the bell pepper and @Mexican style spice mix{2%sachets} to the pan and fry for ~{1%minute}.

Mix in the @passata{1%pack}, beans and @beef stock{1%sachet}.

Bring to the boil, reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until thickened, ~{7-8%minutes}. Season
to taste with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once simmered, stir through the @chipotle paste{1%sachet}.
> TIP: Add a splash of @?water{to taste} if the sauce becomes too dry.

Pop the @tortillas{8} into the oven to warm, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @creme fraiche{65%g} and lime zest to a #small bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir to combine.

Serve warmed tortillas, Mexican spiced mince, zesty creme fraiche and scallion separately.

Allow everyone to assemble their own at the table.

Serve with lime wedges alongside for squeezing over.